<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,956,1100]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
The species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[451,574,956,981]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachypeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,574,956,981]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">Tachypeza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar to the representatives of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1188,1338,956,981]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1188,1338,956,981]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">Tachydromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from them by the presence of vein CuA 
<number box="[851,859,1010,1024]" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" value="2.0">2</number>
. They are usually larger and have largely grey dusted thorax (comparing with 
<taxonomicName box="[524,677,1036,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,677,1036,1061]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">Tachydromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), long slender legs (except fore pair) and narrow wings lacking distinct pattern (at most brownish clouded along veins).
</paragraph>
